messages.message: Hey all, we just merged in a celery configuration change (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/24468) that should make flows recover more quickly from rabbitmq restarts. If you notice any instability on dogfood over the next few days that might be related to this, let us know!
I'm getting `"An unexpected error occurred. (Error=timed out)"` when trying to publish a model in dogfood. could this be a symptom of the instability you mentioned?
I think rabbitmq might be down on dogfood, maybe that's causing it? <#C034HDD7D5E|>
